oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Eisenhower Campaign
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Interior of a school auditorium during Eisenhower campaign. Senator Phillips is the man with his coat open. Big sign with pictures of Eisenhower and Nixon says "Keep America Strong, IKE and Dick, Vote Republican." Students are sitting in the foreground.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Auditoriums; Political campaigns; Political posters; Legislators
